President Cyril Ramaphosa announced the members of his cabinet on Wednesday evening. Courtesy of #DSTV403 PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced the members of his cabinet on Wednesday evening. The number of ministers was reduced by eight seats from 36 to 28 positions. READ: Why Ramaphosa had to delay appointing South Africa's next cabinet The president said the state reconfiguration process has been guided by the need to direct resources to where they will have the greatest impact A number of departments were combined. The presidency announced the following joined portfolios: The portfolios of Communications and Telecommunications and Postal Services were announced as a combined portfolio last year. The president announced he would be signing performance agreements with the ministers and deputy ministers against targets and performance outcomes. The following ministers and deputies were announced: